data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
A bezier curve is an intuitive way of drawing a curve between two points. This is used in this application to draw a keyboard velocity profile or an aftertouch profile.
The diagrams below show examples of velocity profiles that could be used.

data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value:
First, display the Velocity Bezier Curve by selecting^PlayMap Menu > Configure > Bezier > Velocity$.
Then, click on the red circles and drag the mouse to move the spline (straight line) around. This will change the shape of the curve. With a little practice, you can change the curve in almost any way.
You can restore the default at any time with the button at the bottom of the window.
The curve will be saved if you select^PlayMap Menu > File > Save Settings$, or if you choose the Save Settings option on exiting the application.
